org.cleverbus.admin.web.msg
Class MessageOperationController

java.lang.Object
  org.cleverbus.admin.web.msg.MessageOperationController

@Controller
@RequestMapping(value="/operations")
public class MessageOperationController
extends Object

Controller that maps request from the Admin GUI to the message operations:

  • message restart based on the msgID and type. Restart of the message = update the state from FAILED/CANCEL -> PARTLY FAILED in table [message] and [external_call]
  • message cancel - only NEW and PARTLY_FAILED messages can be canceled

Author:
Viliam Elischer, Petr Juza

@RequestMapping(value="/restartMessage",
                method=POST)
public String restartMessage(@ModelAttribute(value="model")
                                                           ModelMap modelMap,
                                                           @RequestParam(value="messageID")
                                                           Long messageID,
                                                           @RequestParam(value="totalRestart",required=false)
                                                           Boolean totalRestart)
The restart method - gets input from web-user and calls a service method for updating the DB record based on the MSG ID.

By default, when the checkbox is on web send as empty = the default value is not annotation driven, but manually setup to false.

Parameters:
modelMap - default view object for adding data to the view resolver (FTL)
messageID - user-input form parameter, used in the restart operation
totalRestart - user-input, if the message should be restarted from scratch
Returns:
name of the view
